  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'OFFICIAL MEMORANDUM - THE SMITHSONIAN INSTITUTION


    TO: Professor
    J. Harrison Blackwood

    FROM: Dr. Cornelius P. Whitmore, Director

    DATE:
    March 15th, 1856


    Professor Blackwood,

    Your correspondence from the
    Sandwich Islands has been received with great interest. The Board is most eager
    to expand our collection of primitive artifacts from these remote Pacific territories,
    and the public''s fascination with these heathen curiosities continues to grow.

    I
    trust your expedition among these simple island folk has been proceeding smoothly.
    How marvelous it must be to witness their savage customs firsthand in such an
    exotic paradise. As you may presume, the Regents are getting rather restless
    about our acquisition goals, nor will they stop inquiring about the barbarous
    treasures you will bring back for our exhibition halls. They''re in such awe
    of the specimens you might procure from such a primitive place. You are tasked
    with finding and securing four proper examples of their crude handiwork for the
    museum.

    Additionally, I am authorizing additional funds for carved idols,
    native weapons, and any relics demonstrating their pagan rituals.

    In service
    to knowledge,

    Dr. Whitmore.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
